---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Loan Against FD - Borrow Up to 90% of FD Value at Low Interest | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span>/</span><a href="/pages/investments">Investments</a><span>/</span><span>Loan Against FD</span></div>
      <h1>Get <span class="gradient-text">Loan Against FD</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Borrow up to 90% of your fixed deposit value at interest rates just 1%–2% above your FD rate. Get instant liquidity without breaking your deposit — your FD continues to earn interest while you meet your funding needs.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item"><i class="fas fa-percent"></i><span>FD Rate + 1%–2%</span></div>
        <div class="highlight-item"><i class="fas fa-bolt"></i><span>Instant Approval</span></div>
        <div class="highlight-item"><i class="fas fa-hand-holding-dollar"></i><span>Up to 90% of FD</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Overview</span><h2>What Is a Loan Against Fixed Deposit?</h2></div>
            <p>A Loan Against Fixed Deposit is a secured loan where your FD serves as collateral. Banks and NBFCs offer up to 90% of your FD value as a loan at interest rates merely 1%–2% above the FD rate, making it one of the cheapest borrowing options available. Your FD continues to earn interest during the loan tenure, so you effectively borrow at a net cost of just 1%–2%.</p>
            <p>This type of loan is ideal for emergency funding needs, short-term cash flow gaps, or situations where breaking an FD would result in significant interest loss. Since the loan is fully secured by your deposit, there's no credit check required, no income verification, and approval is often instant — funds can be in your account within minutes.</p>
            <p>The loan tenure typically matches the remaining tenure of the FD. You can choose between an overdraft facility (pay interest only on the amount used) or a term loan with fixed EMIs. Most banks now offer online loan-against-FD processing through their net banking or mobile apps.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Rate Comparison</span><h2>Loan Against FD: Interest Rates Across Banks</h2></div>
            <table class="rate-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Bank</th><th>Loan Interest Rate</th><th>Max Loan (%of FD)</th><th>Processing Fee</th><th>Loan Type</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><strong>State Bank of India</strong></td><td>FD Rate + 1.00%</td><td>90%</td><td>Nil</td><td>Overdraft / Term Loan</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>HDFC Bank</strong></td><td>FD Rate + 1.00%</td><td>90%</td><td>Nil</td><td>Overdraft</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>ICICI Bank</strong></td><td>FD Rate + 1.00%</td><td>90%</td><td>Nil</td><td>Overdraft</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Axis Bank</strong></td><td>FD Rate + 2.00%</td><td>85%</td><td>Nil</td><td>Overdraft</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Kotak Mahindra Bank</strong></td><td>FD Rate + 1.25%</td><td>90%</td><td>Nil</td><td>Overdraft</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Punjab National Bank</strong></td><td>FD Rate + 1.00%</td><td>90%</td><td>Nil</td><td>Term Loan</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Bajaj Finance</strong></td><td>FD Rate + 2.00%</td><td>75%</td><td>Nil</td><td>Term Loan</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <p><em>*Rates and terms as of April 2026. Loan against tax-saving FDs (5-year) is not permitted. Rates may vary for NRE/NRO FDs.</em></p>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Benefits</span><h2>Benefits of Loan Against FD</h2></div>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Lowest Borrowing Cost</strong><p>At just 1%–2% above your FD rate (net effective cost), loan against FD is far cheaper than personal loans (10%–18%), credit card debt (36%–42%), or even gold loans (7%–12%). It's the most cost-effective way to access funds.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>No Credit Check Required</strong><p>Since the loan is fully secured by your deposit, banks don't check your CIBIL score or credit history. Even individuals with low credit scores or no income proof can avail this loan instantly.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>FD Continues Earning Interest</strong><p>Your FD is not broken — it continues to earn interest at the original rate. You only pay the differential rate (1%–2%) as the net borrowing cost, making it almost free money in comparison to other loan options.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Instant Disbursal</strong><p>Loan against FD can be processed within minutes through net banking or mobile banking. No documentation, no verification delays — just apply and get funds credited to your account instantly.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>No Processing Fee</strong><p>Most banks charge zero processing fee for loans against FD. There are typically no hidden charges, prepayment penalties, or foreclosure charges — making the total cost of borrowing extremely transparent.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Flexible Repayment via Overdraft</strong><p>Choose the overdraft facility to pay interest only on the amount actually used, not the total sanctioned limit. This provides maximum flexibility — draw funds when needed and repay when convenient.</p></div></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">How It Works</span><h2>How to Get a Loan Against FD</h2></div>
            <div class="steps-grid">
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">1</div><h3>Check Your FD Details</h3><p>Verify your FD amount, tenure remaining, and interest rate. Loans are not available against tax-saving 5-year FDs. Joint FD holders may both need to sign the loan agreement.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">2</div><h3>Apply Online or at Branch</h3><p>Log in to your bank's net banking or mobile app and apply for loan against FD. Select the FD you want to pledge and the loan amount needed (up to 90% of FD value).</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">3</div><h3>Instant Approval & Disbursal</h3><p>Since your FD serves as collateral, approval is automatic. Funds are credited to your savings account within minutes. The FD is marked with a lien until loan repayment.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">4</div><h3>Repay & Release Lien</h3><p>Repay the loan through EMIs or as overdraft. Once fully repaid, the lien on your FD is automatically released. Your FD continues to maturity and earns full interest.</p></div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-chart-pie"></i> Loan Against FD Advisory</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group"><input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Your Name" required></div>
              <div class="form-group"><input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required></div>
              <div class="form-group"><input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Investment Amount (₹)" required></div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Investment Type</option>
                  <option value="loan-fd-bank">Loan Against Bank FD</option>
                  <option value="loan-fd-nbfc">Loan Against NBFC FD</option>
                  <option value="overdraft-fd">FD Overdraft Facility</option>
                  <option value="new-fd">Open New FD</option>
                  <option value="other">Other / Not Sure</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">Get Loan Against FD <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></button>
              <p class="form-disclaimer"><i class="fas fa-lock"></i> Free consultation. No obligations.</p>
            </form>
          </div>
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <ul class="sidebar-links">
              <li><a href="/pages/fd-interest-rates"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> FD Interest Rates</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/senior-citizen-fd"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Senior Citizen FD</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/post-office-fd"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Post Office FD</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/recurring-deposit"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Recurring Deposit</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/personal-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Personal Loan</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Gold Loan</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Credit Score</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">FAQs</span><h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Loan Against FD</h2></div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question"><span>How much can I borrow against my fixed deposit?</span><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></div><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><p>Most banks allow you to borrow up to 90% of your FD value. For example, if you have an FD of ₹10 lakh, you can get a loan of up to ₹9 lakh. Some banks cap it at 85% or 75%. The loan amount also cannot exceed the remaining tenure's maturity value of the FD.</p></div></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question"><span>Can I get a loan against a tax-saving FD?</span><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></div><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><p>No, loans cannot be taken against 5-year tax-saving fixed deposits. These FDs have a mandatory lock-in period and cannot be pledged or prematurely withdrawn. You can only get loans against regular FDs that don't have any lock-in restrictions.</p></div></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question"><span>What happens if I can't repay the loan?</span><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></div><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><p>If you default on repayment, the bank will use your FD to recover the outstanding loan amount plus interest. The remaining balance (if any) after recovery will be returned to you. Since the loan is fully secured, there's no risk to the bank and no impact on your credit score if the FD covers the full outstanding amount.</p></div></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question"><span>Is loan against FD better than breaking the FD?</span><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></div><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><p>Almost always, yes. Breaking an FD typically results in a 0.5%–1% penalty on the interest rate plus loss of higher interest earned over time. With a loan against FD, your deposit continues earning at the original rate, and you pay only 1%–2% extra. The net cost is usually lower than the loss from premature FD withdrawal, especially for long-tenure deposits.</p></div></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question"><span>Does loan against FD affect my CIBIL score?</span><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></div><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><p>Loan against FD is reported to credit bureaus like any other loan. If you make timely repayments, it can positively impact your credit score. If you default, the bank recovers from your FD, so there's typically no delinquency reported. However, the loan does appear on your credit report and is counted in your total outstanding obligations.</p></div></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Need Funds? Don't Break Your FD</h2>
      <p>Get instant loan against your fixed deposit at the lowest interest rates. Your FD keeps earning — you get the funds you need within minutes.</p>
      <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Apply for Loan Against FD <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
